sentences: Cuong Vu (born 19 September 1969) is a Vietnamese-American jazz trumpeter.
Born in Saigon on September 19, 1969, Vu immigrated to Seattle with his family when he was six.
After graduating Vu moved to New York City in 1994, and formed the group Ragged Jack with Jamie Saft, Andrew D'Angelo, and Jim Black.
While a member of the Pat Metheny Group, Vu won two Grammy Awards for Best Contemporary Jazz Album: Speaking of Now and The Way Up.
